				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Ordinarily, games time their music engines off the vertical blanking NMI, not the APU Frame IRQ. I think only about two games actually use the APU Frame IRQ. As I understand it, the APU Frame IRQ isn't really for the NES as much as for other applications of a 2A03 CPU with no other source of periodic interrupts.</div>

